      "title": "Winter Breeding Fundamentals: Preparing Your Loft for Cold Weather Pairing",
      "content": "Breeding pigeons through the winter can produce strong early youngsters, but it requires careful planning. In this guide we cover loft insulation, adjusting light schedules, selecting winter breeding pairs, and fine-tuning nutrition. We also outline how to monitor body condition so that hens are not overworked and cocks maintain fertility. Finally, we provide a sample winter breeding calendar that fits most temperate climates.",
